post_text:
Ranger School Only: August 28, 2020

Attention Ranger families. Today, as a result of contact tracing we have received directives that a significant number of the Ranger staff must report for testing and begin quarantine immediately. Although there is not an inordinate amount of positives at the moment, the loss of staff to quarantine will hinder the ability to perform operations and maintain safety of the students at Ranger School. Regrettably we are closing face to face participation immediately and all instruction will be going remote. We are releasing students immediately, so please make arrangements to collect your child or if your child rides the bus, the bus will be leaving school at 11:30 as opposed to the normal dismissal time. We hope this is a temporary circumstance and we will contact you when we are able to resume classes face to face. Thank you in advance for your support and understanding as we encounter these new challenges.

post_text: A community is deeply affected when sudden tragedy occurs without warning. The HDHS School community has many resources available if any of our students, educators or families need support during this tragic time as we mourn the loss of two young HD students. Do not hesitate to contact the principal or central office if emotional support is needed. If you would like to do something in regard to the recent horrific accident that took the lives of 2 young brothers from the HD community, an account has been set up at United Community Bank for the purpose of helping with funeral expenses. Anyone or group or church interested in helping with these expenses for the family may go to United Community Bank in Murphy, Blairsville,McCaysville, or Robbinsville and request the money to be deposited in the HAWKINS BROTHERS MEMORIAL FUND. Thank you and please share this request and continue to pray for the family and friends who have experienced such tremendous loss.....

Reminder: iF YOU or YOU KNOW of a Family in Need: Rotary Club of Murphy is sponsoring a MANNA FoodBank distribution today, Thursday, April 30th at NOON at Murphy Middle. This is for anyone who may be in need.

Cars from those we are serving will line up on Black & Gold Drive (near Sherwin Williams) and depart on Bulldog Drive (near Lowe's.) The cars will pass through the loop at the Murphy Middle School entrance. Volunteers will place a pre-packaged box of food into the trunks or back seats of cars. There will be frozen fish distributed as well so if you have a longer drive and the ability to do so you may want to bring a cooler.

YCC members work on projects that promote awareness and appreciation of the public lands legacy and the nation’s natural, cultural, and historic resources. Congratulations, Jake!

shared_text:
Murphy Middle School
April 7 at 1:09 PM ·

CCS intends to observe Spring Break just as posted on the original School Calendar. This means Good Friday, April 10th will be a holiday and the following week April 13 - April 17 will be spring break. We hope that you all will use this time to disconnect, relax, and focus on time with family. Even though you won't hear from your teachers or school staff next week we are still here!! We will resume our remote learning on April, 20th.

Also, food delivery will be different. Rather than the buses coming each day for meal deliveries, on Thursday, April 9th the buses will be delivering 12 meals in each bag for each student. This will be breakfast and lunch for students for six days.

This means Good Friday, April 10th will be a holiday and the following week April 13 - April 17 will be spring break. We hope that you all will use this time to disconnect, relax, and focus on time with family. Even though you won't hear from your teachers or school staff next week we are still here!! We will resume our remote learning on April, 20th.

Also, food delivery will be different. Rather than the buses coming each day for meal deliveries, on Thursday, April 9th the buses will be delivering 12 meals in each bag for each student. This will be breakfast and lunch for students for six days.

Prek and kindergarten registration for 2020-2021:
Prek and kindergarten registration that was originally scheduled for Friday, March 27 has been postponed. When school is back in session we will reschedule the registration. However, if you would like for your child to attend Prek or Kindergarten in Cherokee County next school year, please call their in district elementary school to have their name placed on the contact list no later than April 10. It is important to have their name on the contact list because these are the students who will be contacted when the registration is rescheduled. If you had already scheduled an appointment for March 27, your child’s name has already been placed on the contact list and you do not need to call again.

Jeana Conley
March 15 at 9:04 PM ·

Attention Cherokee County Families: Tomorrow March 16th we will begin allowing meal pick up at six of our schools. These are Andrews Elementary, Peachtree Elementary, Martins Creek Elementary Middle, Murphy Elementary, Hiwassee Dam School, and Ranger Elementary Middle. Parents and students can pick up the meals (2 at once a breakfast and a lunch for later) between 8am and 1pm. If you need food delivered to your child please call their school or call central office 837-2722 and give Kristie or Cindy your name, address, and numbers of students in your care. The students do not need to be with you to pick up the meals. All school aged students are eligible for free. We are also in the process of working to roll out child care assistance for families who have no alternatives and need to work. Please tell our students that their teachers and principals love them and miss them and will see them again soon. Thank you all for your support during this mandated closure.

text: Due to the threat of impending wintry weather Cherokee County Schools will be closed to students, optional teacher workday for teachers and staff. Any faculty or staff that choose to work, please pay attention to 9 am forecast and do not allow yourself to be caught in hazardous weather. Cherokee County, Clay County, Graham County, Union County and Fannin County share weather and made the same decision.

post_text:
As of right now, Cherokee County Schools is on a regular schedule for Friday February 28th. Cherokee County Schools is monitoring the weather system that is moving in over night. State maintained roads have been driven by county and state employees throughout the county and deemed safe for travel in the morning.

The timeline for this new weather system is extremely inconsistent from all the available sources. If the models in the morning show snow moving in the morning we will close. We will check the timeline in the early morning hours so we have a better understanding of when or if it will hit. A decision will be made before 5:30 am to determine what the best option is to keep our students and staff safe. Thank you for your understanding and patience.

2 Hour Delay, Tuesday February 11th

Update:

The crew has determined a delay will be sufficient- routes are expected to run slower

Due to reports of flooding and anticipated rising of creek water in several areas, Cherokee County Schools will be on a two hour delay, tomorrow, Tuesday February 11. This will enable drivers to see any potential areas impacted by rising waters and make choices in their routes to school. In the event that the flood turns from "watch" status to "warning" we will cancel school, however at this time, CCS will operate on a two hour delay.

shared_text:
Career & Technical Education, Cherokee County, NC is feeling excited.
December 5, 2019 at 10:33 AM ·

The Career and Technical Education (CTE) Department of Cherokee County Schools NC would like to announce the December CTE teacher of the month, Mrs. Rhonda Leblanc!

Leblanc, a National Board Certified teacher, has taught Family and Consumer Science at Hiwassee Dam High School for the past 25 years. Ms. Leblanc teaches Foods and Nutrition classes along with Culinary Arts. She also offers Parenting and Child Development and Advanced Studies classes. Leblanc is proud to be able to offer ServSafe Certification opportunities to her Foods and Nutrition II classes each year.

If you are interested in your student enrolling in these classes or earning their ServSafe Certification, please contact the CTE Coordinator, Meridith Davis at meridith.davis@cherokee.k12.nc.us

Leblanc is proud to be able to offer ServSafe Certification opportunities to her Foods and Nutrition II classes each year.

If you are interested in your student enrolling in these classes or earning their ServSafe Certification, please contact the CTE Coordinator, Meridith Davis at meridith.davis@cherokee.k12.nc.us

This gives all bus drivers and staff and students ample time for day light to be able to see any possible icy patches.

Travel safe-

shared_text:
Murphy Elementary School
September 26, 2019 at 1:38 PM ·

Hello Murphy Elementary community. Today we had a fire in the kitchen at Murphy Elementary as a result of an electrical issue. The cafeteria and school was quickly evacuated and the staff at MES had the fire contained in less than 3 minutes. The Murphy Fire department was quickly on scene and the building was declared safe by the fire chief. As a result of this the cafeteria and lunchroom will be cleaned by a professional cleaning service and new equipment installed. This should be a quick process and we hope to have the cafeteria back open by early next week. In the meantime the staff has made arrangements for breakfast and lunch to be served and temporary serving lines have been set up. During this time the new "Super Snack" will not be served. Otherwise it will be business as usual at MES. Thank you for your support.
